Description: Fix CVE-2026-54278 - Bounded unread compressed drain
 During cleanup of an unread auto-decompressed request body,
 StreamReader._read_nowait could join data fed re-entrantly into the
 buffer (when draining below the low water mark resumes reading) into a
 single unbounded bytes object. A specially crafted compressed payload
 (zip-bomb edge case) could be decompressed into memory in one chunk
 during the drain, leading to denial of service via excessive memory
 consumption and bypassing client_max_size during cleanup.
 .
 The fix snapshots the buffer length when n == -1 and only drains the
 chunks present at call time, so re-entrant resume_reading() refills do
 not get joined into one unbounded result. A call now returns only the
